	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />RockNES passes in all APU tests using the latest findings by Q.
<br />
<br />In fact, if the channel is clocked <em>right with a $4015 read</em>, changes takes effect <strong>only in the next APU clock</strong>, and the same is valid for IRQs. All is justified by the APU/CPU clock ratio of 1:2 (1 APU clock = 2 CPU clocks).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


